`kettle-jem` reads `.kettle-jem.yml` from the project root. The config controls
template sources, README section partials, token values, merge defaults,
per-file strategies, workflow generation, and plugin loading.

<details markdown="1">
<summary>Configuration shape</summary>

```yaml
project_emoji: "💎"
engines:
  - ruby
licenses:
  - MIT
templates:
  root: packaged
  apply: true
  entries:
    - README.md
readme:
  section_partials:
    synopsis: readme/partials/synopsis.md
    configuration: readme/partials/configuration.md
    basic_usage: readme/partials/basic_usage.md
defaults:
  preference: template
  add_template_only_nodes: true
  freeze_token: kettle-jem
patterns:
  - path: "certs/**"
    strategy: raw_copy
files:
  Rakefile:
    strategy: merge
    preference: destination
plugins:
  - kettle-drift
```

</details>

<details markdown="1">
<summary>Strategies, tokens, and freeze blocks</summary>

Template strategies:

| Strategy | Behavior |
|---|---|
| `merge` | Resolve tokens, then merge template and destination using the selected recipe. |
| `accept_template` | Resolve tokens and write the template result. |
| `keep_destination` | Leave the destination file untouched. |
| `raw_copy` | Copy bytes exactly, with no token resolution or merge. |

Merge entries may set `preference`, `add_template_only_nodes`, `freeze_token`,
`file_type`, and `recipe`. `files` entries match exact paths. `patterns`
entries are glob-based and the first match wins.

Tokens use `{KJ\|TOKEN}` syntax. Environment values win over `.kettle-jem.yml`,
and config values win over safe gemspec-derived defaults.

Freeze blocks use the configured token, defaulting to `kettle-jem`:

```ruby
# kettle-jem:freeze
gem "local-only", path: "../local-only"
# kettle-jem:unfreeze
```

Content inside a freeze block is preserved from the destination.

</details>

<details markdown="1">
<summary>Merge engines and workflows</summary>

`kettle-jem` routes files through recipes selected by target path and
`file_type`. Current Ruby recipes cover README metadata/style, changelog
normalization, managed text blocks, GitHub funding, GitHub Actions workflows,
obsolete workflow cleanup, Open Collective cleanup, selected template source
application, and Rakefile scaffold cleanup.

`workflows.preset: framework` generates a Ruby x framework-version CI matrix.
`workflows.coverage` enables coverage workflow generation. Existing custom
workflows can receive pinned-action snippets without replacing the whole file.

`plugins` lists extension gems. A plugin is required by gem name, resolved to a
constant, and called through `register_kettle_jem_plugin(registrar)`. The
registrar supports `before_phase`, `after_phase`, and `on_phase` hooks.

</details>
